                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Beyond delicious! If you are craving some carnitas look no further this spot will not disappoint, it's kinda cafeteria style you walk in order then sit they serve you and if u need anything more you get up and ask they charge you at the end after you have enjoyed your meal. As you walk in you are greeted with a huge smile from the workers and they are beyond friendly you honestly feel like you are home and with family.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Only downfall is I wanted a super spicy salsa but I guess none were spicy enough for me but that's ok, I just added some habanero salsa from the bottle to there homemade salsa that's on the table and boom amazing! Overall please give this place a  chance it will not disappoint if you don't know what to order do the carnitas plate you can easily make 10 tacos with that. Then go from there
                  </span>
                 </p>

                     <path d="M3.06 14.76a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084-2.083V5.344A2.091 2.091 0 0 1 3.06 3.25h1.393l.496-1.487a.75.75 0 0 1 .711-.513h4.334a.75.75 0 0 1 .711.513l.496 1.487h1.74a2.086 2.086 0 0 1 2.083 2.083v7.334a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084 2.083l-9.88.01Zm0-10.01a.59.59 0 0 0-.584.594v7.333a.584.584 0 0 0 .584.584l9.88-.011a.584.584 0 0 0 .584-.583V5.333a.584.584 0 0 0-.584-.583h-2.28a.75.75 0 0 1-.711-.513L9.453 2.75H6.201l-.496 1.487a.75.75 0 0 1-.711.513H3.06Z">
                     </path>
                     <path d="M8 12.556a3.75 3.75 0 1 1 0-7.501 3.75 3.75 0 0 1 0 7.5Zm0-6a2.25 2.25 0 1 0 0 4.5 2.25 2.25 0 0 0 0-4.5Z">
                     </path>
                    </svg>
                   </span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="css-1oibaro" data-font-weight="semibold">
                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/la-mexicana-bakery-and-taqueria-fresno?userid=6YVHRaZymhPXmtNDVSFRKw">
                    2 photos
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   So plenty of people have said this already but this place looks kinda sketchy from the outside - in fact, I couldn't even tell that it was open and there's not a parking lot for it so it's easy to pass right by. However, this place is legit! I had the taco plate with carne asada, adobada, and carnitas and wow. Everything was good but the carnitas was seriously amazing - super savory and flavorful and tender and juicy. The red salsa is also fabulous with just the right amount of heat and a really unique flavor, not just hot. Overall I'm so glad I have this place a try and will definitely return. The staff was very friendly and helpful as well, and if you're into traditional Mexican snacks, candies, and drinks they have plenty of those as well!
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                  <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Mar 21, 2023
                   </span>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <div class="css-1e7audd">
                  <div class="css-5d1n8n">
                   <span alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="icon--16-camera-v2 css-6a0jil" role="img">
                    <svg class="icon_svg" height="16" width="16">
                     <path d="M3.06 14.76a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084-2.083V5.344A2.091 2.091 0 0 1 3.06 3.25h1.393l.496-1.487a.75.75 0 0 1 .711-.513h4.334a.75.75 0 0 1 .711.513l.496 1.487h1.74a2.086 2.086 0 0 1 2.083 2.083v7.334a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084 2.083l-9.88.01Zm0-10.01a.59.59 0 0 0-.584.594v7.333a.584.584 0 0 0 .584.584l9.88-.011a.584.584 0 0 0 .584-.583V5.333a.584.584 0 0 0-.584-.583h-2.28a.75.75 0 0 1-.711-.513L9.453 2.75H6.201l-.496 1.487a.75.75 0 0 1-.711.513H3.06Z">
                     </path>
                     <path d="M8 12.556a3.75 3.75 0 1 1 0-7.501 3.75 3.75 0 0 1 0 7.5Zm0-6a2.25 2.25 0 1 0 0 4.5 2.25 2.25 0 0 0 0-4.5Z">
                     </path>
                    </svg>
                   </span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="css-1oibaro" data-font-weight="semibold">
                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/la-mexicana-bakery-and-taqueria-fresno?userid=lPNsKsD-HvdgkzfGq-Gjig">
                    10 photos
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   As someone who really enjoys Mexican food, I judge how good a taqueria is by the taste of the dishes, their authenticity, the value (quantity, meat portions, condiments, sides) for the price you pay, cleanliness, a good salsa made in-house, a good variety of freshly grilled or stewed meats and daily specials, and lastly, freshly homemade tortillas. While this place does not make homemade tortillas, it meets most of my criteria.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The asada (beef steak) and other beef dishes like the barbacoa de res (stewed beef) seem to get the most positive comments, but many Mexican patrons and I prefer pork at a taqueria because of its versatility when it comes to cooking preparation, tenderness, and juiciness. I appreciate any place that makes full use of the entire swine. The pastor (marinated), carnitas (braised), chile verde (slow-cooked in a roasted tomatillo sauce) and buche (stomach lining) are all very good here. But I have also noticed many customers here wait in the long lines just to order a big slab of chicharron (fried pork rinds). It is unquestionably one of their most popular items on the menu.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Tacos and burritos for take-out and dining in for menudo on weekends are always good choices. Personally, I prefer to dine in to order one of their daily specials or lunch or dinner plates because they come with piping hot tortillas, rice, and beans. This way you have the option to build your own tacos with the tortillas and any remaining tortillas you can use to scoop up whatever is left of your plate.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The plates are also my preference because you get a tremendous amount of food with good portions of meat and you get a lot for your money because the prices are very reasonable. Additionally, La Mexicana serves each plate with its homemade salsa and a stick of Mexican cheese that you allow to melt into the warm refried beans.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Good service is always a bonus and I always feel welcomed here. In addition to being warmly greeted, there usually is one person working that speaks good enough English to understand what you are saying and answer questions.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   This small taqueria is in a very unassuming location in a sketchy part of south-central Fresno but no point bringing up the obvious here. However, once you walk in, you will feel right at home, especially when Victor, the jovial owner-manager is around. He also will not let you leave unless you try a free sampling of other menu items you have not tried yet.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   With the myriad of choices in town when it comes to Mexican food, I have experienced an extremely small sampling of some of the better taquerias out there in my roughly two years as a Fresno resident. I would certainly put La Mexicana as one of my favorites for now with many more places to explore.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Hours are 8 am to 9 pm every day.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Definitely cannot judge a book by its cover...or can you?! Hole in the wall Mom &amp; Pops usually blow me away with delicious home cooking and let me tell you...this place DID NOT disappoint!! The handmade tortillas wrapped around the tender flavor packed asada and carnitas were too good to put down after the first bite. Rice and beans were just like mi abuelitas home cooking yum yum yum!!! Their salsa roja was the icing on the cake and just added that much more flavor to these delicious tacos! They have three aguas otherwise beverage selections are Mexican sodas or canned drinks. Seating isn't too aesthetically pleasing but what they lack in ambiance they deliver in flavor and let's be real do you want a fancy taco place or tacos that stand every tastebud up on your tongue?!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   This place is a MUST TRY...park on the street or risk it in the grocery store parking lot half a block down. Enjoy!!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Was heading home from Yosemite and we were starving. Started reviewing yelp a few miles back and was frustrated that most locations with a five stars only had less than 10 reviews. Stumbled across this one that had a ton of reviews and decided to give it a try.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Definitely do not judge this place from the outside or even the first few steps in. The smell alone was amazing and the staff was friendly.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   We ordered the torta de carne, and the Orden de Carnitas. Both were delicious. Mom and Pop shops can be so hit or miss but this place was a bull's-eye.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The meat was so moist and tender, super flavorful. Rice, beans, and fresh pico topped off a full plate of deliciousness that sent my tastebuds into overdrive.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I'll be making note of this place for the next time we are in the area.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Keep in mind that although they accept card, tips were cash only.
                  </span>
                 </p>

                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Oct 13, 2023
                   </span>

                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Order the carnitas. It is their specialty. It will likely be the best you have ever had. I was told to try the carnitas and ordered 3 tacos. They offer the carnitas "con todos" which comes with some skin and fat, or you can get it much more lean, without the skin and fat. I prefer the latter. It was amazing. The restaurant itself is old and rundown, cement slab, front door looks like is is 40 years past the date that it needed new paint, etc., but that adds to the charm. Feels like you are in Tijuana when you walk in. I hope that doesn't come across as being too negative. I really love this place and will be back again and again.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>
                <div class="arrange__09f24__LDfbs vertical-align-middle__09f24__zU9sE css-1qn0b6x">
                 <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
                  <span class="css-1xfc281">

Taqueria","photoSrc":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_nMTnyPf6hkev_raFzDwhQ/60s.jpg"},"user":{"link":"/user_details?userid=lPNsKsD-HvdgkzfGq-Gjig","src":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/60s.jpg","srcSet":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/ms.jpg 1.67x,https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/120s.jpg 2.00x,https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/90s.jpg 1.50x,https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/168s.jpg 2.80x,https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NXxOx8_JbzfsYdgfATUXEw/180s.jpg 3.00x","markupDisplayName":"Andrew K.","displayLocation":"Clovis, CA","altText":"Andrew K.","userUrl":"/user_details?userid=lPNsKsD-HvdgkzfGq-Gjig","partnerAlias":null,"friendCount":1366,"photoCount":12126,"reviewCount":740,"eliteYear":2023},"comment":{"text":"As someone who really enjoys Mexican food, I judge how good a taqueria is by the taste of the dishes, their authenticity, the value (quantity, meat portions, condiments, sides) for the price you pay, cleanliness, a good salsa made in-house, a good variety of freshly grilled or stewed meats and daily specials, and lastly, freshly homemade tortillas. While this place does not make homemade tortillas, it meets most of my criteria. <br&gt;<br&gt;The asada (beef steak) and other beef dishes like the barbacoa de res (stewed beef) seem to get the most positive comments, but many Mexican patrons and I prefer pork at a taqueria because of its versatility when it comes to cooking preparation, tenderness, and juiciness. I appreciate any place that makes full use of the entire swine. The pastor (marinated), carnitas (braised), chile verde (slow-cooked in a roasted tomatillo sauce) and buche (stomach lining) are all very good here. But I have also noticed many customers here wait in the long lines just to order a big slab of chicharron (fried pork rinds). It is unquestionably one of their most popular items on the menu.<br&gt;<br&gt;Tacos and burritos for take-out and dining in for menudo on weekends are always good choices. Personally, I prefer to dine in to order one of their daily specials or lunch or dinner plates because they come with piping hot tortillas, rice, and beans. This way you have the option to build your own tacos with the tortillas and any remaining tortillas you can use to scoop up whatever is left of your plate. <br&gt;<br&gt;The plates are also my preference because you get a tremendous amount of food with good portions of meat and you get a lot for your money because the prices are very reasonable. Additionally, La Mexicana serves each plate with its homemade salsa and a stick of Mexican cheese that you allow to melt into the warm refried beans. <br&gt;<br&gt;Good service is always a bonus and I always feel welcomed here. In addition to being warmly greeted, there usually is one person working that speaks good enough English to understand what you are saying and answer questions. <br&gt;<br&gt;This small taqueria is in a very unassuming location in a sketchy part of south-central Fresno but no point bringing up the obvious here. However, once you walk in, you will feel right at home, especially when Victor, the jovial owner-manager is around. He also will not let you leave unless you try a free sampling of other menu items you have not tried yet.<br&gt;<br&gt;With the myriad of choices in town when it comes to Mexican food, I have experienced an extremely small sampling of some of the better taquerias out there in my roughly two years as a Fresno resident. I would certainly put La Mexicana as one of my favorites for now with many more places to explore.<br&gt;<br&gt;Hours are 8 am to 9 pm every day.","language":"en"},"localizedDate":"3/21/2023","localizedDateVisited":null,"rating":4,"photos":[{"src":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-3O0NBqdvTOY6dNSyCEtHg/180s.jpg","link":"/biz_photos/la-mexicana-bakery-and-taqueria-fresno?reviewid=u9T57ksdr7cs99qH6EE7qQ&amp;select=-3O0NBqdvTOY6dNSyCEtHg","altText":"Photo of La Mexicana Bakery &amp; Taqueria - Fresno, CA, United States","width":180,"height":180,"caption":null},{"src":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6lAjoJYCEAFPBfsijtcRQA/180s.jpg","link":"/biz_photos/la-mexicana-bakery-and-taqueria-fresno?reviewid=u9T57ksdr7cs99qH6EE7qQ&amp;select=6lAjoJYCEAFPBfsijtcRQA","altText":"Photo of La Mexicana Bakery &amp; Taqueria - Fresno, CA, United States. someone who really enjoys Mexican food, I judge how good a taqueria is by the taste of the dishes, their authenticity, the value (quantity, meat portions, condiments, sides) for the price you pay, cleanliness, a good salsa made in-house, a good variety of freshly grilled or stewed meats and daily specials, and lastly, freshly homemade tortillas. While this place does not make homemade tortillas, it meets most of my criteria. \n\nThe asada (beef steak) and other beef dishes like the barbacoa de res (stewed beef) seem to get the most positive comments, but many Mexican patrons and I prefer pork at a taqueria because of its versatility when it comes to cooking preparation, tenderness, and juiciness. I appreciate any place that makes full use of the entire swine. The pastor (marinated), carnitas (braised), chile verde (slow-cooked in a roasted tomatillo sauce) and buche (stomach lining) are all very good here. But I have also noticed many customers here wait in the long lines just to order a big slab of chicharron (fried pork rinds). It is unquestionably one of their most popular items on the menu.\n\nTacos and burritos for take-out and dining in for menudo on weekends are always good choices. Personally, I prefer to dine in to order one of their daily specials or lunch or dinner plates because they come with piping hot tortillas, rice, and beans. This way you have the option to build your own tacos with the tortillas and any remaining tortillas you can use to scoop up whatever is left of your plate. \n\nThe plates are also my preference because you get a tremendous amount of food with good portions of meat and you get a lot for your money because the prices are very reasonable. Additionally, La Mexicana serves each plate with its homemade salsa and a stick of Mexican cheese that you allow to melt into the warm refried beans. \n\nGood service is always a bonus and I always feel welcomed here. In addition to being warmly greeted, there usually is one person working that speaks good enough English to understand what you are saying and answer questions. \n\nThis small taqueria is in a very unassuming location in a sketchy part of south-central Fresno but no point bringing up the obvious here. However, once you walk in, you will feel right at home, especially when Victor, the jovial owner-manager is around. He also will not let you leave unless you try a free sampling of other menu items you have not tried yet.\n\nWith the myriad of choices in town when it comes to Mexican food, I have experienced an extremely small sampling of some of the better taquerias out there in my roughly two years as a Fresno resident. I would certainly put La Mexicana as one of my favorites for now with many more places to explore.\n\nHours are 8 am to 9 pm every day.&quot;,&quot;__typename&quot;:&quot;ReviewText&quot;},&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.3&quot;:{&quot;node&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;id&quot;,&quot;generated&quot;:true,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.3.node&quot;,&quot;typename&quot;:&quot;Review&quot;},&quot;__typename&quot;:&quot;ReviewEdge&quot;},&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.4.node&quot;:{&quot;encid&quot;:&quot;w2RtcW98-cL0EkVw0YSrAg&quot;,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;id&quot;,&quot;generated&quot;:true,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.4.node.author&quot;,&quot;typename&quot;:&quot;User&quot;},&quot;createdAt&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;id&quot;,&quot;generated&quot;:true,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.4.node.createdAt&quot;,&quot;typename&quot;:&quot;DateTime&quot;},&quot;rating&quot;:5,&quot;text&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;id&quot;,&quot;generated&quot;:true,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.4.node.text&quot;,&quot;typename&quot;:&quot;ReviewText&quot;},&quot;__typename&quot;:&quot;Review&quot;},&quot;$ROOT_QUERY.business({\&quot;encid\&quot;:\&quot;MP3RrCedb3rDTe9l_9WYrA\&quot;}).reviews({\&quot;first\&quot;:20}).edges.4.node.author&quot;:{&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Nue someone who really enjoys Mexican food, I judge how good a taqueria is by the taste of the dishes, their authenticity, the value (quantity, meat portions, condiments, sides) for the price you pay, cleanliness, a good salsa made in-house, a good variety of freshly grilled or stewed meats and daily specials, and lastly, freshly homemade tortillas. While this place does not make homemade tortillas, it meets most of my criteria. \n\nThe asada (beef steak) and other beef dishes like the barbacoa de res (stewed beef) seem to get the most positive comments, but many Mexican patrons and I prefer pork at a taqueria because of its versatility when it comes to cooking preparation, tenderness, and juiciness. I appreciate any place that makes full use of the entire swine. The pastor (marinated), carnitas (braised), chile verde (slow-cooked in a roasted tomatillo sauce) and buche (stomach lining) are all very good here. But I have also noticed many customers here wait in the long lines just to order a big slab of chicharron (fried pork rinds). It is unquestionably one of their most popular items on the menu.\n\nTacos and burritos for take-out and dining in for menudo on weekends are always good choices. Personally, I prefer to dine in to order one of their daily specials or lunch or dinner plates because they come with piping hot tortillas, rice, and beans. This way you have the option to build your own tacos with the tortillas and any remaining tortillas you can use to scoop up whatever is left of your plate. \n\nThe plates are also my preference because you get a tremendous amount of food with good portions of meat and you get a lot for your money because the prices are very reasonable. Additionally, La Mexicana serves each plate with its homemade salsa and a stick of Mexican cheese that you allow to melt into the warm refried beans. \n\nGood service is always a bonus and I always feel welcomed here. In addition to being warmly greeted, there usually is one person working that speaks good enough English to understand what you are saying and answer questions. \n\nThis small taqueria is in a very unassuming location in a sketchy part of south-central Fresno but no point bringing up the obvious here. However, once you walk in, you will feel right at home, especially when Victor, the jovial owner-manager is around. He also will not let you leave unless you try a free sampling of other menu items you have not tried yet.\n\nWith the myriad of choices in town when it comes to Mexican food, I have experienced an extremely small sampling of some of the better taquerias out there in my roughly two years as a Fresno resident. I would certainly put La Mexicana as one of my favorites for now with many more places to explore.\n\nHours are 8 am to 9 pm every
